{"name":"Battle Motto","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character has mastered the rhyming battle motto! If chanted within listening range of an opposing trainer just prior to a battle, it fills the character with pride while simultaneously revolting, boring, and/or irritating their enemy. The opposing trainer suffers a disadvantage on their first two Initiative rolls, while the character gains an advantage on their own first two Initiative rolls. If two trainers chant their own mottoes simultaneously, though, the effects cancel each other out. A motto can only be used once each dramatic scene.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 108","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.l4mNQub2VBCP5xWz"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670148774669,"modifiedTime":1670150619752,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"G7zmQ16SdJQtXOPC"}
{"name":"Instill Discipline","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character is especially talented at making their monsters obey orders and resist their natural urges. Instilling discipline takes a one-hour training session and costs the trainer and monster 10 Energy each. The effects last for one gaming session or adventuring day. A disciplined pet will be cautious during fighting, and it will not lose control or expose itself recklessly. For the discipline duration, the monster gains a +2 Armor Class bonus against attacks.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":"Target is the user's trained monster"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":10},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.M5zgUk5Mku0d24Qu"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670149149886,"modifiedTime":1670150613237,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"Hrs669QS6eU13dAz"}
{"name":"Breed Monster","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>This is the ability to breed two monsters together that do not normally mate, and have them potentially produce viable offspring. If the character makes a successful DC 15 Charisma check, the union of the two monsters is a positive experience, and will likely produce a viable hybrid (as best determined by the storyline). On an unsuccessful check, something goes hideously wrong with the coupling; perhaps they start fighting each other, injury happens during the coupling, the resulting offspring is a horrifying menace, etc.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 108","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"cha","actionType":"abil","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.mBVrJ54h1UJN7sM1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670148849301,"modifiedTime":1670150621045,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"KH5NaYCEdomPXWc8"}
{"name":"Instill Ferocity","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The trainer can instill the fighting spirit in their monster and teach it to go for the quick victory. This technique takes a one-hour training session and costs the trainer and monster 10 Energy each. The effects last for one gaming session or adventuring day, during which time the ferocious monster receives a +2 bonus to its attack rolls. It is also likely to be bad tempered, and may snap at or otherwise harass anyone nearby.</p><p>A trainer can alternatively Instill Ferocity against a specific opponent (such as one specific type of monster). This technique requires appropriate training aids, such as a picture or look-alike doll. This doubles the normal attack bonus to +4, but only against that specific target; the monster does not gain any attack bonus against other opponents. This option is useful if the trainer knows who their monster will face in advance. Monsters can only benefit from one ferocity training session each day.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"hour","cost":1,"condition":"Target is the user's trained monster"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"day"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"attribute","target":"","amount":10},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.HLtLkZQ3JjTKeyed"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670150084133,"modifiedTime":1670150614182,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"PA5qJgybLX2tQqIo"}
{"name":"Analyze Monster","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character can identify all commonly known species of pet monster. They also gain an advantage on Intelligence-related checks required to identify rare types or newly evolved versions of existing species. They can judge another monster's approximate Point total, remaining Hit Points, and any elemental association from its size, species, attitude, apparent health, and even posture, without seeing it actually fight.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 108","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.SKojXvBdefFxVOja"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670148635604,"modifiedTime":1670150618751,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"b4QReRyFKJclL6jW"}
{"name":"Feed Monster","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character knows exactly what to feed their monsters to ensure they have a properly balanced diet. As long as the character can supervise their monster's nutrition (which may take up to a half-hour per creature per day), the monsters will be healthier and happier. They will not catch diseases and will recover lost Hit Points twice as fast as normal. The DM may require the character to devote adventuring time to finding special food, vitamins, or ingredients, or this activity can instead happen in the background between excursions.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"minute","cost":30,"condition":"Target is the user's trained monster"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.eLqhZ4LaDNEV1niH"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670148974219,"modifiedTime":1670150611030,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"ewbyjssnHMR6n2fd"}
{"name":"Inspire Monster","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The trainer is especially talented at inspiring their monster in combat through shouts of encouragement, cheerleading, and other energetic techniques. At the start of any combat round, the trainer can use a free action to spend 5 of their own Energy. This either adds +2 to the monster's attack rolls for the round or +2 to the monster's Armor Class for the round, or it immediately restores 1d8 lost Hit Points to the monster. The character can repeat the expenditure every combat round to continue giving their monster a bonus.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"none","cost":null,"condition":"Start of the round; target is the user's trained monster"},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"round"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.RAIrN6kTO98KVWC1"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670149074905,"modifiedTime":1670150612162,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"pIk2XIkAfJApXjNV"}
{"name":"Stat Master","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character possesses an encyclopedic knowledge of other trainers, as well as teams and monster dojo (if they exist). The character keeps track of who they are, how they rank in any league or organization, and what pet monsters they possess. The DM may require a DC 15 Intelligence check to see if the trainer knows anything about a specific monster or trainer.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"int","actionType":"abil","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.7QH40heL2c1NyVft"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670150600968,"modifiedTime":1670151002714,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"xftL4wE7hynwdkLX"}
{"name":"Monster Tactics","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character has carefully studied monsters in battle. They understand which attack to use for the greatest effect, when to order a finishing blow at the right moment, and when to sound the retreat. The trouble is, it is the monsters fighting – not the character. If the character is supervising a duel, however, and is in a position to shout orders, then all their monsters receive advantages on their Initiative rolls through the battle.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.fgab6R2Gg5bN79mZ"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670150336776,"modifiedTime":1670150621938,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"xh14eAq8cjL6b8tE"}
{"name":"Nurse Monster","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>The character is a monster physician. As long as the monster is under their tender care, it heals Hit Points three times faster than normal. If the character also has the Feed Monster technique, the monster heals five times as quickly instead.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Anime 5E p. 109","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"requirements":"Monster Training","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"equipped":false,"attuned":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"destroyFlavorText":"reaches 0 charges: it crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.","rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1","sorting":"l"},"core":{"sourceId":"Actor.s4Ozg63igYR1agM6.Item.kovjBzKWnuikLf0u"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1670150524593,"modifiedTime":1670150623122,"lastModifiedBy":"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gk3gL94MefjaC4oW":3},"_id":"z2WALAlVNBtuiC1s"}
